==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|en|pride goes before a fall|pride goeth before a fall|pride wenteth before a fall|pride cometh before a fall}}
* {{alter|en|pride comes before the fall}}

===Etymology===
Probably a misquote of:
* '''1611,''' [[w:King James Version of the Bible|King James Version of the Bible]], [[w:Book of Proverbs|Book of Proverbs]], [[s:Bible (King James)/Proverbs#Chapter 16|16:18]],
*: Pride goeth before destruction, and a haughty spirit before a fall.

===Proverb===
{{head|en|proverb}}

# A person who is excessively [[proud]] will often suffer a [[setback]] or [[failure]].

